# How to run plugin
Script named kubectl-kubeplugin has to be copied to /usr/local/bin/ and granted execution permissions
after that it can be run with the following syntax:
kubectl kubeplugin <namespace> <command> <resource>

Example:
kubectl kubeplugin default top pods
This will display the CPU and Memory usage of all pods in the default namespace:

kubectl kubeplugin argocd top nodes
Resource,Namespace,Name,CPU,Memory
nodes  argocd  fast-k01-dev  1742m  80026Mi
nodes  argocd  fast-k02-dev  720m   68029Mi
nodes  argocd  fast-k03-dev  770m   67496Mi
nodes  argocd  hellout       608m   26674Mi
nodes  argocd  km1           206m   1746Mi
nodes  argocd  km2           123m   1976Mi
nodes  argocd  km3           105m   2151Mi

